The paper deals with optimization problems in directed graphs with random arc lengths, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several sub-categories in computer science. The use of risk measures and the evaluation of algorithm performances suggest that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a likely sub-category. The proposed algorithms and the use of stochastic lower bounds suggest that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible sub-categories. The optimization aspect of the paper and the use of constraints suggest that cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of experiments and the evaluation of performances suggest that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible sub-category as well.
